# {{wiki_name}} wiki configuration

This file holds wiki-specific configuration that the agent reads on every command. The structural schema is described in `CLAUDE.md` and in `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/skills/wiki-setup/SKILL.md`. Edit the frontmatter to change the configuration; do not edit `CLAUDE.md`.

## Field reference

- **name**: display name shown in `/help` and reports.
- **slug**: short identifier used as the wiki argument to every command (e.g. `/ingest <slug> ...`). Pick something short.
- **root**: absolute filesystem path to the wiki root. Must match the registry.
- **entry_points**: each one has `path` (relative to root), `source_type` (must be one of the buckets in `wiki-core` SKILL.md), `default_quality` (override the bucket default), `post_ingest` (`move` or `keep`), `naming_convention` (plain-English description; the agent applies it during monthly archival).
- **structured_knowledge**: each has `path`, `purpose` (one of `projects`, `documentation`, `resources`, `people`, `concepts`, `custom`), `routing_hint` (free text used by `/ingest` to decide what goes here).
- **dashboards**: paths to files the agent must not modify as a side effect (todo, canvas, etc.).
- **protected_paths**: structured-knowledge subfolders that `/rebuild` must not clear (hand-written content like recipes, manual references).
- **project_thresholds**: month counts after which active projects are suggested for dormant, dormant ones for archive, completed ones for archive.
- **tags**: tag vocabulary used across the wiki. Agent uses these on new pages where applicable.
- **writing_style**: free-form prose rules. The agent applies these to every page it writes.

## Free-form notes

Anything below this line is for your own reference. The agent reads it but does not apply it programmatically.
